comment: Global offset is -1.4 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure.  GelMA (T1) and HAMA (T2). Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), + 600 µL (layer 3). Vol. T2: 600 µL (layer 2). Washing channels: dipping, then rinsing 3x1 mL warm DPBS with pipette, removing excess liquid with KimWipe (touching channels). 1print with big air bubble in last layer (-->pos 6), 2 with tiny bits of channels missing, rest good. Overall little overcuring on all prints.   All R&g using T1-221201. Transferring all at the same time into separate 24-wells with 0.5 mL 2x Hase in ECGM2 +P/S (221201MF ).
